cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it focuses on network analysis and link prediction in complex systems such as social networks. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) as it proposes new methods for solving the link prediction problem. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of various techniques to improve link prediction. It may also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with the analysis and prediction of complex systems. Finally, it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new concept (ALC) and improves existing methods for solving a fundamental problem in network analysis.
